access:
Guests will have access to a private 1 bedroom apartment including a private backyard.  They will have access to their own fully equipped kitchen, dining room, living room, bedroom, plenty of closet space with hangers, towels, blanket, pillows, ironing board and iron, full bathroom and private backyard (rare find in New York).

The apartment has its own private entrance inside the house, is cable TV ready, has Wi-Fi internet (high speed), door buzzer, private backyard.

We offer a light "Welcome Breakfast" (self-serve) for your arrival day.
additional_house_rules:
We love our neighborhood and respect our neighbors; we want to keep our home as clean, inviting, comfortable and as secure as possible, therefore, it is our hope that you understand the need for the below house rules and details: 

Bedding/Towels:  Guests to change bedding and towels if staying for longer periods of time, using linens and towels provided by the hosts.  Extra bed sets, towels, blanket & airbed can be found in the bedroom closet.  Should you need extras in addition to those items, please contact us (happy to provide).

Cooking: Light cooking only

Damages:  Guests are responsible for any damages done to the apartment & its belongings during their stay.  Absolutely no eating/drinking in bed or on the couch.  Blue & white design pillows in the bedroom are strictly decorative, please do not sleep on them. 

Dishes/Utensils/Coffeemaker/Toaster:  Guests need to clean / wash dishes/utensils, coffeemaker, toaster & refrigerator prior to checking out of the apartment

Events/Parties/Illegal Activities:  Absolutely no parties or events allowed - this is a private home in a residential area.  No illegal activities allowed.

Extra Guests:  No extra guests / visitors allowed other than those noted in the booking

Keys & Check-Out:  The apartment keys are on the kitchen countertop.  When ready to check-out, please send us a text message in advance and leave the keys on the kitchen countertop.

Loud Music/Noises:  No loud music or noises before 8AM or after 10PM

Lost items: Hosts not responsible for any items guests leave behind

Parking: Street parking

Rain/Snow:  If it rains/snows, please remove your shoes before entering the apartment (shoes/boots tray by the apartment’s front door).  Please also be mindful of rain/snow when re-entering the apartment from the backyard as to not damage the carpet. Thank you for your cooperation.  

Recycling:  Guests need to recycle paper/carton and plastic/metal/glass in the designated bins under the sink (clear bag under sink for paper/carton items; blue bag for plastic/metal items; white bag in the kitchen garbage can for household trash).  

Restaurants/Menus: There are lots of restaurants and take-out/catering venues in our area.  You will find take-out menus on the kitchen countertop.
-	For food deliveries, use the house address & provide them with your cell phone number to call you upon arrival.  Alternatively, ask them to ring the bottom bell by the front door.  When you hear the bell, open the front door of the main house to greet them.

Shower: If the shower makes noise when you turn it on cold water, keep turning it toward warm/hot water and the noise will stop.  Nothing to worry about, just wanted to make you aware. 

Smoking: This is a non-smoking apartment.  Absolutely no smoking allowed inside.  Smoking is permitted only in the backyard.

Taxi: In addition to Uber or Lyft; local cab numbers: (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)

TV:  You have access to Fios TV and High-Speed Internet 

WiFi Network ID:  D5JDM_Ext		WiFi Code:  5C8RSLYLQWQJ7PD2
description:
Our place is close to public transport (easy/quick commute to Manhattan), JFK and LGA airports, the park, beach, nightlife, activities and lots of good restaurants including well-known Arthur Avenue in Bronx's Little Italy (7mins via car /famous for its amazing/authentic restaurants). You’ll love our place because of the chic decor, coziness, neighborhood, location, easy access to Manhattan & lots of convenience stores.  Our apartment is good for couples, solo adventurers and business travelers.

You will enjoy a newly renovated private apartment with quality stainless steel appliances, brand new modern furniture and beautiful artwork throughout the apartment & a private backyard (rare find in New York).

The apartment is cable TV ready (Fios) and guests will have Wi-Fi access to internet (high-speed).

Our place is located in Pelham Bay / Bronx.

We take pride in maintaining our place spotless and fresh so that each trip will become a great & memorable experience for our guests.

Guests will have access to a private 1 bedroom apartment including a private backyard.  They will have access to their own fully equipped kitchen, dining room, living room, bedroom, plenty of closet space with hangers, towels, blanket, pillows, ironing board and iron, full bathroom and private backyard (rare find in New York).

The apartment has its own private entrance inside the house, is cable TV ready, has Wi-Fi internet (high speed), door buzzer, private backyard.

We offer a light "Welcome Breakfast" (self-serve) for your arrival day.

We will be more than happy to offer help throughout your stay with us.  We live upstairs and are accessible whenever you need us, always with a smile and glad to help in any way we can in order to make your stay with us an excellent experience.

Our neighborhood is a safe, residential area with quick/easy access to Manhattan (easy 5 minute walk to subway & you will only need to take 1 train to get there (no need to change/switch to any other trains); you will get to Manhattan within 40 mins). 

Plenty of groceries, dry-cleaning/laundromat, restaurants, 24/7 Rite Aid,  hair salons, manicure/pedicure, shopping mall, convenience stores and more, all within minutes from our place.  

Plenty of good restaurants and take-out (lots of italian restaurants & great pizza, thai / asian, carribbean, 2 great italian bakeries).

If you love the outdoors or a great walk /  run in the park, New York's largest park awaits you just 5 minutes walking distance from our place.  You also have easy access to Orchard Beach (7 minutes via car or you can also take a bus nearby).

Shopping mall is minutes away from our place via car or via bus (5 minute walk to bus).

We live in a very safe area with convenient and quick access to public transportation (5 minute walk to subway; if driving, 2-3 minute access to highways).

Getting to Manhattan is very easy: you will only need to take 1 train and will be there within 35-40mins (walk to subway is 5 minutes).

Street parking for those who have a car. Important to follow parking signs if you park in a restricted area.

Sleeping set-up: 
- queen size bed in the bedroom (sleeps 2)
- queen size air mattress (sleeps 2)

Our motto is "Carpe Diem."  We wish you an exceptional time visiting our great city and we look forward to having you stay in our home.
